== 天气和气候 ==
天气是指一个地区短时间局部的，临时的大气现象。

[[气候|气候]]是指一个地区长时间（比如30年）的大气平均物理状态。

==预报==
{{Main|天气预报|天气谚语}}
[[File:Day5pressureforecast.png|thumb]]
[[File:Paul-McCrone-DMSP-F18-FClr-Day-Fog-Stratus-Fullq-281641Z-DEC-10_1293583405.jpg|缩略图]]

天气预报将科技应用于预测[[地球大气层|大气]]在未来时刻的指定地点的状态。百万年以前人类就一直试图预测天气，直到19世纪才开始有了正式的天气预报。<ref>{{dead link|date=June 2011}} Mistic House. [http://www.mistichouse.com/astrology-lessons.htm Astrology Lessons, History, Prediction, Skeptics, and Astrology Compatibility.] {{Wayback|url=http://www.mistichouse.com/astrology-lessons.htm |date=20080608133837 }} Retrieved on 12 January 2008.</ref><ref>Eric D. Craft. [http://eh.net/encyclopedia/article/craft.weather.forcasting.history ''An Economic History of Weather Forecasting''.] {{Wayback|url=http://eh.net/encyclopedia/article/craft.weather.forcasting.history |date=20070503193324 }} Retrieved on 15 April 2007.</ref>天气预报需要收集当前大气状态的定量数据，然后运用我们[[气象学|对大气过程的科学理解]]来预测大气将如何变化。<ref>[[NASA|NASA]]. [http://earthobservatory.nasa.gov/Library/WxForecasting/wx2.html Weather Forecasting Through the Ages.] {{Wayback|url=http://earthobservatory.nasa.gov/Library/WxForecasting/wx2.html |date=20050910210732 }} Retrieved on 25 May 2008.</ref>

开始是完全依靠人力来根据[[气压|气压]]变化、当前天气状况以及天空情况做预报，<ref>Weather Doctor. [http://www.islandnet.com/~see/weather/eyes/barometer3.htm Applying The Barometer To Weather Watching.] {{Wayback|url=http://www.islandnet.com/~see/weather/eyes/barometer3.htm |date=20080509105153 }} Retrieved on 25 May 2008.</ref><ref>Mark Moore. [http://www.nwac.us/education_resources/Field_forecasting.pdf Field Forecasting: A Short Summary.] {{Wayback|url=http://www.nwac.us/education_resources/Field_forecasting.pdf |date=20090325034756 }} Retrieved on 25 May 2008.</ref>现在则使用[[数值天气预报|预报模式]]预测未来的天气。人力仍然被需要用来挑选最可能优秀的预报模式来做预报，需要考虑模式识别技巧、[[遥相关|遥相关]]、模式效能以及模式偏差。大气的[[混沌理论|混沌]]本质、求解描述大气的方程组所需的大量的计算资源、在测量初始情况时所带来的误差、以及对大气过程的仍不完整的理解，种种这些因素使得预报的越早以及预报的时间（预报''范围''）越长则预报结果越差。[[集合预报|集合预报]]的使用可以帮助我们减小误差和挑选出最可能的结果。<ref name="Klaus">Klaus Weickmann, Jeff Whitaker, Andres Roubicek and Catherine Smith. [http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/spotlight/12012001/ The Use of Ensemble Forecasts to Produce Improved Medium Range (3–15 days) Weather Forecasts.] {{Wayback|url=http://www.cdc.noaa.gov/spotlight/12012001/ |date=20071215055130 }} Retrieved on 16 February 2007.</ref><ref name="TBK">Todd Kimberlain. [http://www.hpc.ncep.noaa.gov/research/TropicalTalk.ppt Tropical cyclone motion and intensity talk (June 2007).] {{Wayback|url=http://www.hpc.ncep.noaa.gov/research/TropicalTalk.ppt |date=20131016231757 }} Retrieved on 21 July 2007.</ref><ref>Richard J. Pasch, Mike Fiorino, and [[Chris_Landsea|Chris Landsea]]. [http://www.emc.ncep.noaa.gov/research/NCEP-EMCModelReview2006/TPC-NCEP2006.ppt TPC/NHC’S REVIEW OF THE NCEP PRODUCTION SUITE FOR 2006.]{{dead link|date=2017年12月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} Retrieved on 5 May 2008.</ref>

天气预报有各种各样的终端用户。天气警报被用于保护生命和财产，是重要的预报。<ref>[[National_Weather_Service|National Weather Service]]. [http://www.weather.gov/mission.shtml National Weather Service Mission Statement.] {{Wayback|url=http://www.weather.gov/mission.shtml |date=20131124214601 }} Retrieved on 25 May 2008.</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.meteo.si/met/en/app/webmet/#webmet==8Sdwx2bhR2cv0WZ0V2bvEGcw9ydlJWblR3LwVnaz9Ccy92ZvIXZhxWbvkWbhdWZvA3bp5GdugXbsxXZ1J3bwVGfp1WYnVGf7R2btFWaupzJzx2b2VmbpF2JsAXYyFWblRXZypzJTFEVFxETJRVRfxUQUV0UUdSf; |title=National Meteorological Service of Slovenia |access-date=2012-09-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120618145647/http://www.meteo.si/met/en/app/webmet/#webmet==8Sdwx2bhR2cv0WZ0V2bvEGcw9ydlJWblR3LwVnaz9Ccy92ZvIXZhxWbvkWbhdWZvA3bp5GdugXbsxXZ1J3bwVGfp1WYnVGf7R2btFWaupzJzx2b2VmbpF2JsAXYyFWblRXZypzJTFEVFxETJRVRfxUQUV0UUdSf; |archive-date=2012-06-18 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>基于气温和[[降水|降水]]的预报对农业很重要，<ref>Blair Fannin. [http://southwestfarmpress.com/news/061406-Texas-weather/ Dry weather conditions continue for Texas.] {{Wayback|url=http://southwestfarmpress.com/news/061406-Texas-weather/ |date=20090703095038 }} Retrieved on 26 May 2008.</ref><ref>Dr. Terry Mader. [http://beef.unl.edu/stories/200004030.shtml Drought Corn Silage.] {{Wayback|url=http://beef.unl.edu/stories/200004030.shtml |date=20111005203246 }} Retrieved on 26 May 2008.</ref><ref>Kathryn C. Taylor. [http://pubs.caes.uga.edu/caespubs/pubcd/C877.htm Peach Orchard Establishment and Young Tree Care.] {{Wayback|url=http://pubs.caes.uga.edu/caespubs/pubcd/C877.htm |date=20081224112403 }} Retrieved on 26 May 2008.</ref><ref>[[Associated_Press|Associated Press]]. [http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9D0CE5DB1E30F937A25752C0A967958260  After Freeze, Counting Losses to Orange Crop.] Retrieved on 26 May 2008.</ref>因而也受到股票和[[期货|期货]]市场里那些[[大宗商品|大宗商品]]交易者的重视。公共事业公司也依靠气温预报来估计未来的需求。<ref>[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]. [http://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9F0CE7D9123AF935A15751C0A965958260  FUTURES/OPTIONS; Cold Weather Brings Surge In Prices of Heating Fuels.] Retrieved on 25 May 2008.</ref><ref>[[BBC|BBC]]. [http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/uk/5212724.stm Heatwave causes electricity surge.] {{Wayback|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/uk/5212724.stm |date=20090520060913 }} Retrieved on 25 May 2008.</ref><ref>Toronto Catholic Schools. [http://www.tcdsb.org/environment/energydrill/EDSP_KeyMessages_FINAL.pdf The Seven Key Messages of the Energy Drill Program.] {{Wayback|url=http://www.tcdsb.org/environment/energydrill/EDSP_KeyMessages_FINAL.pdf |date=20120217042744 }} Retrieved on 25 May 2008.</ref>每日里，人们参考天气预报来决定日常的穿戴。因为户外活动会被大雨、雪以及[[风寒指数|寒风]]所严重影响，人们依靠预报来计划活动和为坏天气做些预先准备。

